# Festag — popup body copy (kompletter Satz)

In **modals, sheets, and popups**, usually include a **longer full sentence** (kompletter Satz) under/near the title or as the first body intro — **colored to match the theme**.

## Do

- Prefer a calm, complete German sentence that explains what the dialog is for
- Place it in the **body** (e.g. `.auth-rec-body p`, modal intro), not as a page `h1` lead
- **Light:** calm dark / readable muted text (e.g. `#5c5c62` or `--fp-muted` on light surfaces — not near-invisible gray)
- **Dark / OLED:** light muted on popup surface (e.g. `rgba(245,245,247,0.68)` or `--fp-muted`) — never leave light-mode black/gray stuck on dark panels

## Don't

- Incomplete muted half-sentences or question fragments under the title  
  Bad: `Passwort vergessen oder E-Mail unsicher?`
- Wrong theme contrast (dark-mode body still `#1e1e20` / `#5c5c62` without dark overrides)
- Treat this as permission for **page** leads under route `h1` — those stay forbidden

## Distinguish from other Festag copy rules

| Surface | Lead / intro under title |
|---|---|
| Page `h1` (settings, portal lists, etc.) | **No** subtitle / `.set-page-lead` — see `festag-no-page-leads` |
| Modals / sheets / popups | **Yes** — longer full sentence, theme-correct color |
| Kickers / eyebrows | Still **no** — see `festag-no-kickers` |
| Middle dots in meta joins | Still **no** — see `festag-copy-separators` |

## Good pattern

```tsx
<h2 className="…-title">Zugang wiederfinden</h2>
<div className="…-body">
  <p>
    Wenn du dich nicht mehr anmelden kannst, setze dein Passwort zurück,
    fordere einen neuen PIN an oder schreib uns — wir helfen dir weiter.
  </p>
  {/* fields / actions */}
</div>
```

When touching existing popups that only show a title + CTAs, add a proper body sentence and verify light + dark theme colors.
